Class OutputKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.rules.OutputKey
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<OutputKey>

    public class OutputKey
extends Object
implements Comparable<OutputKey>
    OutputKey encapsulates computation of SHA-1 content hashing for outputs.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      OutputKey(File output)
      OutputKeys that have no associated outputs (output == null) are treated as sentinels that are distinct from other idempotent OutputKeys.

    • Method Summary

      int compareTo(OutputKey other)

      int hashCode() 
      boolean isIdempotent() 
      boolean isSentinel() 
      String toString() 
      String toString(boolean mangleNonIdempotent)
      Sentinel OutputKeys are output as a string of 's' characters, and non-idempotent OutputKeys are normally output as a string of 'x' characters, but when comparing two sets of OutputKeys in textual form it is necessary to mangle one of the two sets, so that non-idempotent OutputKeys are never considered equal.

    • Constructor Detail

      • OutputKey

        public OutputKey(@Nullable
         File output)
        OutputKeys that have no associated outputs (output == null) are treated as sentinels that are distinct from other idempotent OutputKeys. OutputKeys associated with actual outputs are non-idempotent if the outputs cannot be read during key generation.
